You are working in the `site` monorepo.

Always do first:
- Read `CLAUDE.md`.
- Read `AGENT_MEMORY.md`.

Repo map:
- `static-site/`: production portfolio site (Vite + React + TypeScript + Tailwind, Framer Motion, GSAP, Lenis).
- `game-site/`: platformer portfolio concept, early development.

Working conventions:
- Default implementation target is `static-site/` unless the user explicitly asks for `game-site/`.
- Run commands from the correct project directory, not the repo root.
- Before concluding frontend changes in `static-site/`, run:
  - `npm run lint`
  - `npm run build`
- Keep visual style aligned with existing design system (forest palette, glass cards, gradients, motion-rich interactions).
- Prefer small, incremental edits and avoid broad rewrites unless requested.
- Do not introduce heavy dependencies without explicit approval.

Architecture memory:
- `static-site/src/sections/` holds full-page sections used by `src/App.tsx`.
- `static-site/src/components/` holds reusable UI/background components.
- `static-site/src/hooks/` contains scroll and animation hooks.
- `static-site/src/styles/index.css` has Tailwind directives and custom utility layers.
- `static-site/vite.config.ts` uses `base: "./"` for portable static deployment.

Delivery style:
- Be concise and implementation-first.
- When done, report changed files and verification commands run.
